Bio-Community version 0.01
==========================

THIS MODULE IS IN EARLY DEVELOPMENT STAGE! WHILE IT CURRENTLY PROVIDES USEFUL
OPERATIONS, THE INTERFACE MAY UNDERGO CHANGES TO IMPROVE THE MODULES.

Bio::Community is a set of BioPerl modules to represent and manipulate communities
of biological organisms.


INSTALLATION

To install this module type the following:

   perl Build.PL
   ./Build
   ./Build test
   ./Build install


DEPENDENCIES

This module requires perl 5.10 or above. Additionally, these perl modules are
required:

  BioPerl version > 1.6.910
  Bio-Root 1.7 (bundled here)
  DateTime
  Getopt::Euclid
  JSON::XS
  Hash::Util
  Math::Random::MT
  Method::Signatures
  Moose
  Moose::Util::TypeConstraints
  MooseX::NonMoose
  MooseX::StrictConstructor
  Parallel::Iterator
  PerlIO:eol
  Scalar::Util
  Tie::IxHash
  Test::Number::Delta

These other modules are recommended:
  Clone::Fast
  Math::BigInt::GMP


